hooks.prompt:
If stop_hook_active is true, respond {"ok": true}.

Otherwise, read the transcript at transcript_path. If the session already captured its meaningful outputs with summarize_work, respond {"ok": true}.

If not, decide whether the session produced either:
1. meaningful work (code changes, decisions, debugging, research), or
2. durable reusable knowledge from the user (project answers, requirements, explanations, processes, or historical context that would help in a future session).

Skip trivial sessions such as brief Q&A, simple file reads, greetings, transient coordination, ask-expert queries without meaningful outcomes, or one-off logistics. Do not ask to log secrets.

Trivial or already logged: {"ok": true}
Meaningful work not logged: {"ok": false, "reason": "Call mcp__plugin_halyard_ask-expert__summarize_work with a title and summary of what was accomplished."}
Durable user knowledge not logged: {"ok": false, "reason": "Call mcp__plugin_halyard_ask-expert__summarize_work to capture the reusable knowledge from this session. Use entry_type DECISION, PROCESS, or CONTEXT as appropriate."}
